\begin{rem}\label{rem: D(eta) is convex}
Note that $D(\eta), \cV_m$ and $\RR^n\backslash\cW_m$ are convex. Also, $\eta\in D(\eta)$ and $-\eta\in H(\eta)\setminus D(\eta)$ since
$
	\brk{-\eta,\undim P}=\brk{\undim P,\eta} > 0
$
for all projective modules $P$. Furthermore, $D(\eta)$ contains all regular roots $\rho=\undim R$ where $R\in\cR$ since these are exactly the roots which lie on $H(\eta)$ and satisfy $\Hom_\Lambda(R,M)=0$ for all preprojective $M$ (making $\brk{\rho,\alpha}\le0$ for $\alpha$ preprojective).
