We recall the following properties of these regions.

\begin{prop}[See \cite{BHIT}, Section 4]\label{prop: regions}

	\begin{enumerate}
	\item $\cV_m\cap H(\eta)=D(\eta)$
	\item $\cW_m\cap H(\eta)=H(\eta)\setminus D(\eta)$.
	\item For all $T$, the interior of $R(T)$ lies either entirely in $\cV_m$ or in its complement.
	\item For all $T$, the interior of $R(T)$ lies either entirely in $\cW_m$ or in its complement.
